## 4. Key User Flows

### A. User Authentication Flow

The system employs client-side session management. Route guards ensure that protected pages redirect unauthorized users to the login screen.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Browser
    participant auth.js
    participant database.js

    User->>Browser: Enters credentials & clicks Login
    Browser->>auth.js: Auth.login(email, password)
    auth.js->>database.js: get(USERS)
    database.js-->>auth.js: Return users array
    auth.js->>auth.js: Verify credentials
    alt Valid Credentials
        auth.js->>database.js: set("currentUser", sessionToken)
        auth.js-->>Browser: Redirect to Dashboard
    else Invalid Credentials
        auth.js-->>Browser: Show Error Toast Notification
    end
```

### B. Book Browsing & Request Flow

Users can dynamically filter through an extensive catalog of books seeded into the system.

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> BrowseBooks
    BrowseBooks --> FilterByCategory: Select Category
    BrowseBooks --> SearchText: Type in Search Bar
    FilterByCategory --> RenderResults
    SearchText --> RenderResults
    RenderResults --> BookDetails
    
    BookDetails --> ClickRequest: If not owner
    ClickRequest --> RequireAuth
    
    RequireAuth --> Login: Not Logged In
    RequireAuth --> ExchangeSystem: Logged In
    
    ExchangeSystem --> CreateRequest: Validate Book Availability
    CreateRequest --> [*]: Toast Success & Send to Owner
```

