## 8. Detailed Role Breakdown

The system enforces strict Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) to ensure security and manageability even within a client-side simulated database.

### 1. Guest (Unauthenticated User)
*   **Landing Page ([index.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/index.html)):** Can view the hero section, site features, and briefly browse the "Recently Added" books preview.
*   **Authentication ([login.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/login.html), [register.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/register.html)):** Can create a new account or sign in to an existing one. Guest route guards prevent logged-in users from accessing these pages.

### 2. Regular User (Authenticated User)
*   **Dashboard ([dashboard.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/dashboard.html)):** Acts as the homepage post-login. Displays personalized statistics (Books Listed, Pending Requests, Successful Exchanges) and quick status updates.
*   **My Books ([my-books.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/my-books.html)):** The personal inventory manager. Users can view their owned books, track their "available" vs "exchanged" status, and delete un-exchanged books.
*   **Add Book ([add-book.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/add-book.html)):** The form interface to grow the system's inventory. Users supply title, author, category, condition, description, and an optional image URL.
*   **Browse & Request ([browse-books.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/browse-books.html)):** The marketplace. Users can search textually or filter by category. They can issue "Requests" on any book they do not own.
*   **Exchange Management ([exchange-requests.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/exchange-requests.html)):** Bi-directional request tracker. 
    *   *Incoming:* Accept or reject requests from others who want their books.
    *   *Outgoing:* Monitor the status (pending, accepted, rejected) of requests they've made for others' books.
*   **Profile ([profile.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/profile.html)):** Account settings page to edit display name or credentials.
*   **Advanced Features:** Full access to Community Forums, Leaderboards, AI Recommendations, and Book Clubs.

### 3. Administrator (Super User)
*   **Inherits All User Permissions:** Admins can perform any action a regular user can.
*   **Admin Dashboard ([admin.html](file:///f:/college%20projects/BOOKEXCHANGESYSTEM/admin.html)):** A specialized analytical view hidden from regular users.
    *   *System Metrics:* Macro-level statistics showing total users, total books across the platform, and total exchange requests historically made.
    *   *User Management:* Tabular view of all registered accounts with the God-mode ability to forcefully delete disruptive users.
    *   *Inventory Management:* Global oversight of all books in the database. Admins can moderate the platform by deleting inappropriate or spam book listings regardless of ownership.

